messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Explanation:
- The class is annotated with @Path("/api/v0/ops/node") and the repair method is annotated with @Path("/repair"), so the full endpoint path is the concatenation: /api/v0/ops/node/repair.
- The repair method is explicitly annotated with @POST, and it returns/produces MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN. There are no annotations for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, PUT, DELETE, or PATCH on this method.
- The "All methods acceptable" flag is false because there is an explicit @POST and no indication in the code that every HTTP method is accepted.
- Although some JAX-RS implementations may provide implicit handling for HEAD and OPTIONS (e.g., HEAD delegating to GET or automatic OPTIONS responses), the requirement was to base acceptability strictly on the code annotations. Since there is no @HEAD or @OPTIONS method in this source for this path, those methods are reported as not acceptable.
